
(Cmd + Espacio) y escribir "Terminal".

######## INSTALAR Homebrew ###########
ejeuctar los siguintes comandos
    /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

    (los siguientes tres comandos se pueden ejecutar juntos)
    echo >> /Users/madb/.zprofile
    echo 'eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"' >> /Users/madb/.zprofile
    eval "$(/opt/homebrew/bin/brew shellenv)"

validar instalacion con siguinte comando

brew --version








####### INSTALAR JAVA  ###############
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BWC8sRfd09I
https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/#jdk21-mac

java --version
/usr/libexec/java_home -V
nano ~/.zshrc
export JAVA_HOME=$(/usr/libexec/java_home)
export PATH=$JAVA_HOME/bin:$PATH
echo $JAVA_HOME








####### INSTALAR PSQL, CLIENTE PARA POSTGRES DESDE TERMINAL  ###########

brew doctor
brew update
brew install libpq
brew link --force libpq


NOTA: lo siguinte no se hizo, seria ver para que se realiza, que beneficios trae
libpq is keg-only, which means it was not symlinked into /opt/homebrew,
because it conflicts with PostgreSQL.

/*
